&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About QuantHealth&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At QuantHealth, we are reshaping the pharmaceutical industry by eliminating the $45B annual loss caused by clinical trial failures. &lt;br&gt;Our cutting-edge, in-silico clinical trial simulation platform uses a massive pharmaco-clinical foundation model trained on over 100 million patient records. &lt;br&gt;Trusted by global pharmaceutical leaders, we simulate thousands of trial variations to predict patient-level responses, optimize trial designs, and calculate the Probability of Technical Success (PTS) with an 85%+ accuracy rate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking a Senior Product Manager to own the full product lifecycle of our core Clinical Trial Simulation Product: from day-to-day execution with engineering to longer-term roadmap decisions. &lt;br&gt;This role is at the intersection of statistics, product management, and hands-on rapid development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ll be the primary PM driving delivery, managing the backlog, and working directly with pharma stakeholders to turn complex clinical needs into clear, shippable products. &lt;br&gt;This is a hands-on, high-ownership role for someone who thrives in fast-moving environments and can operate confidently at the intersection of data-heavy products and real user problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Ownership: Own the end-to-end product lifecycle for our core Clinical Trial Simulator backlog, sprint planning, prioritization, and delivery in close partnership with engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Translation: Partner with pharma users and internal domain experts to turn complex clinical workflows into clear, well-scoped product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Execution: Serve as the connective tissue between data science, engineering, and commercial teams and keep delivery moving without losing sight of user impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User Discovery: Run continuous discovery with pharma stakeholders to surface high-value problems, validate assumptions, and pressure-test solutions against real clinical workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-Informed Decisions: Use product analytics, user feedback, and clinical data context to prioritize what gets built and measure whether it&#39;s working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI Tooling: Leverage AI development tools where useful to prototype, explore, and accelerate early-stage product thinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 5+ years of Product Management, specifically on complex, data-heavy, or B2B SaaS platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execution Track Record: Proven ability to own a product end-to-end - backlog to launch - in a fast-paced environment with high autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Mindset: Comfortable with data, metrics, and quantitative concepts. A background in statistics, biostatistics, data science, or engineering is a strong plus. Prior exposure to healthcare, clinical trials, or life sciences is also valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builder Instinct: Experience working hands-on with data or prototyping tools (Python, SQL, or AI coding environments) is preferred but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication: Able to work across highly technical teams and translate complexity into clear decisions and crisp product specs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
